Package it.polimi.ingsw.model.board

Class Deck<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.ingsw.model.board.Deck<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object that makes up the "cards" of the Deck.
    public class Deck<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Decks are ordered collections of objects from which it is only possible to remove, and then read, one object at a time.

      • smartDraw

        public java.util.Optional<T> smartDraw​(boolean autoRegenerate)
        Attempts to draw from the Deck. If the draw was successful, an Optional containing the drawn card is returned If, instead, the draw failed because the Deck is empty, if autoRegenerate is false, an empty optional is returned. Otherwise, if autoRegenerate is true, the Deck is regenerated from the discard pile and shuffled, then a second attempt to draw a card occurs. If the Deck is empty again, an empty optional is returned, while if a card was successfully drawn, it is returned as optional.
        Parameters:
        autoRegenerate - whether or not to regenerate and shuffle for a second attempt after a possible failure.
        Returns:
        Either an empty optional, or an optional containing a card, as described above.
